# Test Writing Best Practices

## 1. Use Descriptive Test Names

```typescript
// Bad
test('test1', async ({ page }) => { });

// Good
test('user can login with valid credentials', async ({ page }) => { });
```

## 2. Follow AAA Pattern

**Arrange, Act, Assert**:

```typescript
test('user can add todo', async ({ page }) => {
  // Arrange - Setup
  await page.goto('/todos');

  // Act - Perform action
  await page.fill('.new-todo', 'Buy milk');
  await page.press('.new-todo', 'Enter');

  // Assert - Verify result
  await expect(page.locator('.todo-list li')).toHaveText('Buy milk');
});
```

## 3. Keep Tests Independent

Each test should:
- Not depend on other tests
- Set up its own data
- Clean up after itself (Playwright does this automatically)

```typescript
// Bad - depends on previous test
test('login', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.fill('#email', 'user@test.com');
  await page.click('#submit');
});

test('view profile', async ({ page }) => {
  // Assumes user is already logged in!
  await page.goto('/profile');
});

// Good - each test is independent
test('user can view profile after login', async ({ page }) => {
  // Login first
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.fill('#email', 'user@test.com');
  await page.click('#submit');

  // Then test profile
  await page.goto('/profile');
  await expect(page.locator('h1')).toHaveText('My Profile');
});
```

## 4. Use Meaningful Selectors

```typescript
// Avoid
await page.click('div > div > button');

// Better
await page.click('button[type="submit"]');

// Best
await page.click('button:has-text("Sign in")');
// Or with data-testid
await page.click('[data-testid="submit-button"]');
```

## 5. Add Multiple Assertions

Verify all relevant aspects:

```typescript
test('successful login', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.fill('#email', 'user@test.com');
  await page.fill('#password', 'password');
  await page.click('#submit');

  // Multiple assertions ensure complete verification
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');
  await expect(page.locator('.welcome')).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.locator('.user-name')).toHaveText('John Doe');
  await expect(page.locator('.logout-button')).toBeVisible();
});
```

## 6. Group Related Tests

```typescript
test.describe('User Authentication', () => {
  test('successful login', async ({ page }) => { });
  test('login with wrong password', async ({ page }) => { });
  test('login with non-existent user', async ({ page }) => { });
});
```

## 7. Use beforeEach for Common Setup

```typescript
test.describe('Todo Tests', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    // This runs before each test
    await page.goto('/todos');
  });

  test('add todo', async ({ page }) => {
    // Page is already at /todos
    await page.fill('.new-todo', 'Task 1');
  });

  test('delete todo', async ({ page }) => {
    // Page is already at /todos
    await page.click('.delete-button');
  });
});
```
